After her hair-raising arrival at the Village, Kate, 40, toured the centre cash-strapped parents with clothes, toys and essentials. Wearing a cream Zara blazer and trousers, she bonded with mum Sara and her children, aged three and 18 months, in Brent, north-west London. The beaming royal said: "You forget how tiny they are," before adding: "remember those days. It's a busy time...but so wonderful." " Helping Sara select some books, plucked Michael Rosen's We're Going A Bear Hunt." The duchess revealed a favourite of her children, George, Charlotte, seven, and Louis, four - absent yesterday after being a cheeky for his mum during the Jubilee celebrations. Sara later said Kate was "very kind, sweet and very lovely. I'm very happy I met her."